			<ns0:name>shcherb...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105197577636354702799/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Some instructions are manually splitted in def files by operand size.

Sometimes three variants are listed:
rexw=0, no data16
rexw=0, data16
rexw=1, no data16

Sometimes, there are four of them:
rexw=0, no data16
rexw=0, data16
rexw=1, no data16
rexw=1, data16 (nacl-forbidden)


Since r10783 gen_dfa when splitting instructions automatically does not produce fourth option (rexw=1, data16), so perhaps it makes sense to remove it from .def files as well for consistency.
